org.subjectj.compositor.build

Class ClassBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.subjectj.compositor.build.ClassBuilder

  • public class ClassBuilder
extends Object
    Allows for the composition of a new class file from the contents of other class files. Uses the Builder design pattern so the steps could easily be chained, i.e. into a composite function.
    Author:
    John Rivera

        newClassName - The name of the composed class that will result from the build.

    • Method Detail

      • composeClass

        public ClassBuilder composeClass(String className1,
                                 String className2)
        Composes two class files into the new composed class. The behavior is simple; all contents from the second class file will be appended onto the first. In other words, this method performs a concatenation operation on the two classes.
        Parameters:
        className1 - The mapped name of the first class file to be composed.
        className2 - The mapped name of the second class file to be composed.
        Returns:
        A ClassBuilder with the updated composed class.

      • mergeByName

        public ClassBuilder mergeByName(String className1,
                                String className2)
        Merges all methods in two class files by name. In other words, all methods with the same names in the first and second class files will be merged into a new method with the same name. This method calls mergeMethods in the implementations; see the documentation for that method for more details. Use with caution; this method is under development and likely to change.
        Parameters:
        className1 - The mapped name of the first class file merged.
        className2 - The mapped name of the second class file merged.
        Returns:
        A ClassBuilder with the updated composed class.

      • mergeMethods

        public ClassBuilder mergeMethods(String className1,
                                 String methodName1,
                                 String className2,
                                 String methodName2,
                                 String newMethodName)
        Merges two methods into one with a new name. The second method will be appended onto the first; in other words, this means all instructions in the first method will be called, followed by the instructions in the second. This method is then appended to the composed class.
        Parameters:
        className1 - The mapped name of the class file containing the first method to be merged.
        methodName1 - The name of the first method to be merged.
        className2 - The mapped name of the class file containing the second method to be merged.
        methodName2 - The name of the second method to be merged.
        newMethodName - The name of the resulting method. Normally would be the name of one of the methods above, but could optionally be anything.
        Returns:
        A ClassBuilder with the updated composed class.

      • overrideMethods

        public ClassBuilder overrideMethods(String className1,
                                    String methodName1,
                                    String className2,
                                    String methodName2,
                                    String newMethodName)
        Overrides a method with another. This method simply replaces the instructions from the first method with the instructions from the second and places this into a new method. This method is then appended to the composed class.
        Parameters:
        className1 - The mapped name of the class file containing the method to be overridden.
        methodName1 - The name of the method to be overridden.
        className2 - The mapped name of the class file containing the overriding method.
        methodName2 - The name of the overriding method.
        newMethodName - The name of the resulting method. Normally would be the name of one of the methods above, but could optionally be anything.
        Returns:
        A ClassBuilder with the updated composed class.

      • overrideFields

        public ClassBuilder overrideFields(String className1,
                                   String fieldName1,
                                   String className2,
                                   String fieldName2,
                                   String newFieldName)
        Overrides the contents of a field with another, and stores this in a new field. This field is appended to the composed class.
        Parameters:
        className1 - The mapped name of the class containing the field to be overridden.
        fieldName1 - The name of the field to be overridden.
        className2 - The mapped name of the class containing the overriding field.
        fieldName2 - The name of the overriding field.
        newFieldName - The name of the resulting field. Normally would be the name of one of the fields above, but could optionally be anything.
        Returns:
        A ClassBuilder with the updated composed class.

      • write

        public Path write(String classFile)
           throws IOException
        Finalizes and writes the composed class to a file. Finalizes the composed class by removing all duplicate members -- only the last occurring duplicate members in the file are retained. Then writes this to the file specified by the parameter.
        Parameters:
        classFile - The path to the file to be written to. If the file already exists, it will be overwritten without prompt.
        Returns:
        The Path representing the new file.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs writing to the specified file.
